4/13/2026
Returning to the project after a few months (maybe closer to six).   Currently working on bug hunting and migrating to a compatible combination of tailwind and daisy. upgraded to postcss tailwind 4. added Server model architecture to allow a server agnostic front end, and finally have an excuse to invite more users as we would no longer be constrained by my home server setup.  This will hopefully lead to a front end redesign focusing on the new options. Future "for fun" goal is to upgrade the memory game to allow art generated with the modeler, and deepen the gameplay. For now, having the site morph into something with a consistent focus is the primary over-arching goal.

5/4/2026
I'd say that the last dev notes started my process of daily working on this project again, and while I haven't been keeping dev notes, I feel quiote productive. I've done a complete overhaul of the component/Model system, making a streamlined front end that follows the same pattern for all primary models. Every front end piece is model-manager, model-gallery, add-model, model-footer, and model-interact. I've trimmed a LOT of extra components, and, possibly coincidence, dropped average build time from 3:30 minutes to 2:50. Rebuilt the memory game with a dungeon theme. reorganized all front end bits )app.vue, page [...slug].vue, and layouts/default.vue for better division of label. And finally broke the butterflies from from their frankensteined component and into the store for database supported unique butterflies and smarter pathing. Redesigned the front end layout for a modular sidebars, footer, and header, with a finally pleasing arrangement of front end buttons that don't interfere with the rest of the page. built out the Server model and connected to allow  the user to switch between art and text modelers (still work in progress). Built out the Dream model for multiplayer text and image chat rooms. Still in development, but the inspiration for the major model redesign. Re-connected stable diffusion and comfy servers, though this weekend's taks will probably involve completing those connections. Rebuilt brainstorm and got working text based feedback. Got themes to work whether showing daisy ui themes or user created ones.

All in all I feel very accomplished and productive. The front end doesn't look like ass, and the future roadmap feels doable with some serious accomplishments ahead as long as I stick with it.

