5/17/2026
Wow, ten days ago I was excited about a working handshake. Since I've got 90% of the backend working, with image generation through SD, testing and front end with a working tailscale connection. 

Built an admin accessed line from ChatGPT to Kind Robots for object gen in app. Still troubleshooting uploading of images to the database, but can update text fields. Waiting to setup auth for user access before release. Current projects involve migrating out of the Art objects and directly using artImages for all image data. This will hopefully create a lot less friction with image creation/handling, and speed production. The other project is creating the builder system to walk the user through creating pitches, art, dreams, rewards, characters, and scenarios (bots to be a future add, have some ideas to make a bot a more functional addition to the project by letting the user dictate the scope of the return fields.) Overall made significant improvements to the UI, eliminated the footer, moved the header to a bottom base, and overall worked towards a more focused and minimalist layout. There is still a lot of pieces, but the overall site is much more navigable and the pieces flow into each other better.

I would still like to make progress on the multi-user potential for the site. I feel like getting an end to end build system and testing a few more connection systems (comfy, openai images, anthropic), should have us primed for users to bring their own server setup. I also need to setup a straightforward system for people to demo the site using my resources, but the ideal setup for that uses a self-hosted text processor, which I have yet to implement.

