5/21
a productive weekend. scaffolded out code workbench and it looks better than I expected. 
finished bug hunting after removing Art, Gallery, and Tag from the database. Plan to replace with Art Image, Collection, and Pitch. The trickiest part was interstitial as I tried to make both work. with AI based development, it reaply makes sense just to run in the direction you want to go. I spend too much time trying to appease multiple systems.

disabled comfy as a cypress test suite, but built out api endpoints for various comfy tasks. Cool to think that things like 3d model generation are just a template change difference from art modeling.

i put openai and abthropic at the same task for designing the code workbench, but openai returned first ao we used its design. Claude reported that the final design was beyond its initial pitch, which makes sense, but I did appreciate how it's pitch dealt with models influencing text and images. i'm not using it's framework, as I think processing models into text and images should be the model codse's duty, but it got me thinking about how to allow, and support, high level model interactions


5/25/2026
My adhd jumping from focus to focus may need to be studied.  scaffolding the character builder and just loving how it's coming out. Lots of time spent modeling art. 

I refreshed the front end styling through anthropic. built out tests for art and text through wonderlab. redesigned dashboard shell two dozen or so times to troubleshoot tab memory issues, but they should now be resolved.

Character builder included the "adventure" folder, though the adventure to a character is quite mundane. I am in love with much of the art that has been created. I may be in a minority, but there are pictures that hit emotional resonance for me, and communicate an idea, and broaden a universe. I love this part of project generation. I added so many quirks, personally, before giving the list to ai, to get my list of 75 or so quirks expanded to 150, which then dropped to 101. The art was very much chatGPT, however, I gave very minimal guidelines, other than style requests and asking that they present characters that are multidimensional, not conventionally gendered, bodied, or necessarily humanoid.

